"Subject\'s Rights: If you have read this form and have decided to participate in this project, please understand your participation is voluntary and you have the right to withdraw your consent or discontinue participation at any time without penalty or loss of benefits to which you are otherwise entitled. "Time Involvement: You can participate for as long as you want by keeping the app installed."

"Description: HabitLab is a research study on developing better online habits. You can participate by installing and using the HabitLab Android app. The app will ask you to specify some goals (such as spending less time on Facebook), and will deploy various interventions that aim to help you achieve those goals. It will log data related to progress on your goals (such as time spent on domains), which will be used by our algorithms to determine which interventions work for you. Data will not be shared with anyone outside our research team."
"HabitLab is a research project run by the Stanford HCI Group."
